@NODE intro "Introduction"
@{u}Introduction@{uu}

   This is a door which allows you to put questions to and get answers from
your callers, it allows you to get everyone to answer it (eventually) or only
just the new users depending on where you run it, OR maybe a simple
questionnaire for stuff like polls and that, its up to you!

Features
~~~~~~~~
- The Questionaire directories can be located anywhere on your hard drive, 
  and you can have an unlimited amount too.

- Funky effective (and centred!) ANSI.

- The User.Dat file (containing the names of the peeps who have already used it)
  can be edited with a simple ASCII ed (add/delete any names you want).

- Designed to be run from anywhere on your BBS and be about anything.

- `Hotkeys' for single key press answers. `Pre-set hotkeys' for Yes/No,
  Male/Female, etc. type answers.

- Creates questionnaires readable from any standard ASCII viewer, with
  questions included for easy reading - and if they just hit return it
  reports `skipped'. Same with a dropped carrier.
 
   Anyway, have a cruise of this guide, check out all the relevant sections
and stuff, oh and don't forget to contact @{" me " LINK credits} if you decide
to use it, because I like to know these things! (I can't believe I wrote that
a year ago :)..)

@ENDNODE


