@NODE History "History"
@{u}History@{uu}

4.1 - Fixed path bug (Bippy M), it works now :).

      Made a lot of internal text look nicer, improved layout and display
      of some parts of the program.
      
      Added date & time & nicer format to questionnaire outputs.
      
      Added Yes/No, Male/Female, Agree/Disagree pre-set hotkey answers (Lanky).
      
      Added @{"Bye.text" LINK install 99} which can be used to stop the internal "Thanks
      for completing" text from displaying, by displaying your own :).
      
      Hotkeys are now capitalised.
      
      Re-wrote in KewlDoors by Niki Murkett, optimised and made the code a
      lot nicer!
      
      Updated some outdated guide stuff & coding practice.
      
4.0 - KingQuest 4.0 (by Steve Clack, an update to MagicKingQuest 1.0 AKA
      KingQuest 2.0), now tell me you're not confused :).

      Back in AMOS, cos Tom's C version was never finished and was worse than
      my AMOS one. <G>
      Upto 72 characters per answer line.
      MAXs only now.
      Only uses memory that it needs to.
      Multinode compatible.
      Rewritten code, MUCH MUCH better.
      Lots and lots more, its got a new config format so re-read!

3.0 - KingQuest 3.0 (by Tom Bampton).

      Increased line width limit, rewrote in C and changed the questionaire
      format a bit. No known bugs.

2.0 - Actually named MagicKingQuest 1.0 (added to the /X\agic series).

      Fixed loader, now accepts commas to be entered and kept as commas :)
      Added a little 'maximum you can write' > < 's (you'll see what I mean).
      All auto centring questions and answers (watch out for odd numbers)
      All QUESTIONS and ANSWER PROMPTS are CENTRED, for a WIKID effect!
      >> PARAGON COMPATIBLE << with special custom pause feature.
      FIXED MY SPELLING ERRORS :) I must have been SLIGHTLY tired!
      Added optional Message.Text for each questionaire.
      'Hotkey' one keypress feature.
      Multi-line answer support.
      Now accepts # to terminate the reading of the config too.
      Internally is a lot better and more efficent.
      >> Don't forget MAXs peeps to use the %Z parameter!! <<

1.0 - Initial release. No bugs yet ;)

@ENDNODE
